The paper focuses on runtime monitoring of cyber-physical software to prevent unexpected misbehavior or failure. This involves detecting abnormal states through the use of invariants. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE), Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a new approach, CoMID, which involves context-based trace grouping and multi-invariant detection, indicating a possible connection to Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
